","parent":"85","text":"gram-negative\\Nbacteria","guid":"SObog9mCniwRjP8wgg0Qrw","children":[{"id":"88","parent":"87","text":"fourth generation cephalosporin","guid":"hxvGpzMn1YCa7nFwoEYQ8g","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"87","text":"carbapenem","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"87","text":"beta-lactam/beta-lactamase inhibitor","guid":"iNJ8jLIHMX5PcTMtaZha9Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"91","parent":"85","text":"aminoglycoside in\\Ncombination therapy","guid":"5iC07mxnMv92igc5VTt3dQ","children":[{"id":"92","parent":"91","text":"balanced against the known\\Nnephrotoxicity and ototoxicity associated","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"93","parent":"85","text":"neutropenia, severe illness/sepsis, or known\\Ncolonization with resistant gram-negative bacteria","guid":"TIF1CDBEmuziGzkYet4sZA","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"antimicrobial combination therapy for multidrug resistant bacteria\\Ngram-negative bacilli (such as \\\\/Pseudomonas aeruginosa\\\\/)","guid":"6DcsXYvSomJfpXYuO7iq1w","children":[]}]},{"id":"95","parent":"85","text":"critically ill patients with suspected\\NCRBSI involving femoral catheters","guid":"5bgWMnBtiIOaI4b-gPB60w","children":[{"id":"96","parent":"95","text":"gram-negative bacilli and\\N\\\\/Candida\\\\/ species","guid":"dIdAgyZYFTf0D4dWr2PjCw","children":[]}]},{"id":"97","parent":"85","text":"empiric antifungal therapy for patients with sepsis\\Nand suspected catheter-related candidemia","guid":"75x1sKd1nhCKj6ykRq6RhQ","children":[{"id":"98","parent":"97","text":"when the following risk\\Nfactors are present","guid":"","children":[{"id":"99","parent":"98","text":"total parenteral nutrition","guid":"jKe1Uy0sDprrwS4eE2Iw1Q","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"98","text":"prolonged use of broad-spectrum antibiotics","guid":"DRMiYh7f0V3_TeJPKDaxkQ","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"98","text":"hematologic malignancy","guid":"On9lUcUJF_PMjuU4L-j15g","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"98","text":"bone marrow or organ transplant recipient","guid":"YPfg0JJVJlJZQ0ZgAjsMfw","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"98","text":"femoral catheterization","guid":"67n8vez3V9FXIq8Kn0Tc0w","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"98","text":"known colonization of multiple sites with candida species,","guid":"WTGdOT3-Uq6YxZzmkzRuDw","children":[]}]},{"id":"105","parent":"97","text":"Manejo con","guid":"","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"echinocandin or fluconazole","guid":"DDSWmTlWSbN_oklzzbn2QQ","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"107","parent":"84","text":"Antimicrobial regimen should be\\Nmodified to target specific pathogens","guid":"nMdxdKmOm2CI6lcGCK4oLQ","children":[{"id":"108","parent":"107","text":"Staph. aureus","guid":"1TGD1Q5ngljniLKRk3DbGA","children":[{"id":"109","parent":"108","text":"Remove catheter as salvage therapy\\Nhas a high rate of failure","guid":"ZqJl7FiCgZZgzALUFcDcow","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"108","text":"Vancomycin 15-20 mg/kg IV q8-12h to achieve preferred target AUC24 400-600 μg/mL x\\Nhr (see vancomycin AUC dosing calculator; alternative is trough of 15-20 μg/mL) x\\Nminimum of 2 weeks (longer if associated with endocarditis or osteomyelitis)","guid":"6SfYbjceauStEub4iKGYSQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"111","parent":"107","text":"Staph. epidermidis","guid":"Rmkm7Pfq1qVRzR4Cug5rAg","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"Can try to \"save the catheter\"","guid":"QpiWT13L-OJQIyzbp7CxoQ","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"111","text":"Vancomycin x 10-14 days (with catheter lock technique) if\\Ncatheter retained, or for 5-7 days if catheter is removed.","guid":"ykMRNotixqziEp6y5keDBA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"114","parent":"84","text":"Duration of therapy is based on causative organism and patient characteristics","guid":"-Ie-JLVP6xIN4Y_1oXAEBA","children":[]}]},{"id":"115","parent":"83","text":"Indications for\\Ncatheter removal","guid":"24T5u_rTe8MhjYYpFJIEmA","children":[{"id":"116","parent":"115","text":"Long-term catheters should be removed from patients\\Nwith catheter-related bloodstream infection and","guid":"lBmFvemRD6Ji1pNXr-EBHA","children":[{"id":"117","parent":"116","text":"severe sepsis","guid":"mZD9ahL0Zn4_D2D1xPlvZQ","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"116","text":"suppurative thrombophlebitis","guid":"aNPmlNcfVNK2P2yn3DLJCw","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"116","text":"endocarditis","guid":"o_cooY4dLSnLyalUak-R2Q","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"116","text":"persistent bloodstream infection despite\\N72 hours of effective antimicrobial therapy","guid":"SO8qOcvMVJTru8NKcd5jtg","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"116","text":"infections due to \\\\/Staphylococcus aureus\\\\/,\\N\\\\/Pseudomonas aeruginosa\\\\/, fungi, or mycobacteria.","guid":"Zrud9mIY2uCRDb4MtRjDhg","children":[]}]},{"id":"122","parent":"115","text":"Short-term catheters should be removed from patients\\Nwith catheter-related bloodstream infection due to","guid":"ISuInPJyuT5VUWitqEuNDw","children":[{"id":"123","parent":"122","text":"gram-negative bacilli","guid":"1A0JC2FkrqNELvqxM8E4WQ","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"122","text":"\\\\/Staphylococcus aureus\\\\/","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"122","text":"enterococci","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"122","text":"fungi","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"122","text":"mycobacteria","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"128","parent":"83","text":"Catheter\\Nretention","guid":"KaJ8zB0plI6oi8aFoUiwhA","children":[{"id":"129","parent":"128","text":"considered in patients with extremely limited alternative vascular access sites\\Nand/or excessive complications associated with catheter removal and replacement","guid":"1YuTmqqr2CMRHI8aZXhf2Q","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"128","text":"Procedimientos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"131","parent":"130","text":"Antimicrobial lock therapy with systemic antimicrobial therapy\\Nshould be considered in patients with catheter retention (Weak recommendation).","guid":"gW6kBqr1ZPHVpBfg8GoNsw","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"130","text":"antimicrobial lock-therapy cannot be used, systemic antibiotics should be\\Nadministered through colonized catheter (Weak recommendation).","guid":"YYyJ9rOtrkaL2fYnr2Y5iw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"133","parent":"83","text":"patients with infected\\Nhemodialysis catheter","guid":"T42dILIhwsdgL0M-UpxTVQ","children":[{"id":"134","parent":"133","text":"Remove infected catheter in patients with CRBSI due to \\\\/S. aureus\\\\/,\\N\\\\/Pseudomonas\\\\/ species, or \\\\/Candida\\\\/ species and insert temporary catheter\\N(nontunneled) at separate anatomical site (Strong recommendation).","guid":"KiD8ul--g_z6M4us8BLQdA","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"133","text":"If no alternative site for catheter insertion, exchange infected\\Ncatheter over guidewire (Weak recommendation).","guid":"m2gn9dSDpRHOSwDaCHgBug","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"133","text":"long-term hemodialysis catheter may be\\Nplaced once blood cultures are negative\\N(Weak recommendation).","guid":"4PK1lnUqMCKtHW9ZaQtPdw","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"133","text":"Initiating empiric antibiotic therapy without immediate catheter removal may be\\Ndone for CLABSI due to other pathogens, such as coagulase-negative\\Nstaphylococci or gram-negative bacilli other than \\\\/Pseudomonas\\\\/ species.","guid":"rJCBITTSswD-XRiW5Td_FQ","children":[{"id":"138","parent":"137","text":"remove catheter if","guid":"QgdgmE0rPdn2PU-vIfHc-g","children":[{"id":"139","parent":"138","text":"symptoms which\\Nprompted empiric therapy","guid":"1-bPgkj0cDbBjLODLPxWDg","children":[{"id":"140","parent":"139","text":"fever, chills, unstable blood pressure\\Nor mental status changes","guid":"8usfDqvFPC4nXQuwKbQ3LQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"141","parent":"138","text":"persist or evidence of\\Nmetastatic infection","guid":"G-djYHp-X-nSWuV0f4JTqA","children":[]}]},{"id":"142","parent":"137","text":"New long-term hemodialysis catheter can be exchanged over guidewire if symptoms\\Nprompting systemic therapy resolve within 2-3 days and no evidence of metastatic infection","guid":"r0evOrOak6ROmL-eRKjEuA","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"137","text":"If catheter removal\\Nnot indicated","guid":"kpvKqfAlH5JCnfGFvui1zA","children":[{"id":"144","parent":"143","text":"resolution of symptoms and bacteremia in 2-3 days following\\Ninitiation of systemic therapy and absence of metastatic infection","guid":"VK6J_0VU_CETh0eyvxbMxw","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"143","text":"antibiotic lock can be used as adjunctive therapy\\Nafter each dialysis session for 10-14 days","guid":"ZmAFPwWSTXeSNNU4eJduVQ","children":[]}]}]}]}]},{"id":"146","parent":"0","text":"Prevención","guid":"kwlpho6HNnF1-m2wRRhmSw","children":[{"id":"147","parent":"146","text":"skin preparation\\Nwith chlorhexidine","guid":"0ls6GnTJ-O_DUw4x-kjMEQ","children":[{"id":"148","parent":"147","text":"chlorhexidine contraindicated,\\Nuse povidone-iodine or alcohol","guid":"IZyEZTBfvKJKa2DysBQqhw","children":[]}]},{"id":"149","parent":"146","text":"proper catheter insertion technique\\Nand insertion site selection","guid":"ZPGkbpbFwovkTfSe-MBRBg","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"146","text":"use of maximal sterile\\Nbarrier precautions","guid":"cpig3lskBLKkvzzI6oMOFw","children":[{"id":"151","parent":"150","text":"long sleeve sterile gown, sterile gloves, cap,\\Nmask, and sterile full body patient drape .","guid":"mGXXDAnQXXtIGZL0nG9xKg","children":[]}]},{"id":"152","parent":"146","text":"proper hand hygiene","guid":"ccyz9-SDLrrXWly2oK_zTw","children":[{"id":"153","parent":"152","text":"palpating catheter insertion sites and before and after inserting,\\Nreplacing, accessing, repairing, or dressing an intravascular catheter","guid":"d0tS0oQcLiUxn9ehV1ZXjw","children":[]}]},{"id":"154","parent":"146","text":"covering catheter site with sterile gauze or sterile, transparent,\\Nsemi-permeable dressing, and replacing if damp, loosened, or visibly soiled","guid":"UuyOmzi-x